import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.plot(data['date'], data['open'], color='blue')
    ax.set_xlabel('Date')
    ax.set_ylabel('Opening Price')
    ax.set_title('What is the trend of the opening price over time?')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.show()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    data['day'] = data['date'].dt.day_name()
    data = data.groupby('day').mean().reset_index()
    plt.bar(data['day'], data['volume'])
    plt.axhline(y=data['volume'].mean(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Average Volume')
    plt.xlabel('Day of the Week')
    plt.ylabel('Volume')
    plt.title('What is the average daily volume of trades?')
    plt.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    data = data.set_index('date')
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='high', kde=True, ax=ax, color='blue')
    ax.axvline(data['high'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Mean: {data['high'].mean():0.2f}")
    ax.axvline(data['high'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Median: {data['high'].median():0.2f}")
    ax.set_xlabel('High Prices')
    ax.set_ylabel('Frequency')
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of daily high prices?')
    ax.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import numpy as np

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    data = data.sort_values(by='date')
    data['daily_return'] = (data['close'] - data['open']) / data['open']
    avg_daily_return = data['daily_return'].mean()
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.plot(data['date'], data['daily_return'], color='blue')
    ax.axhline(avg_daily_return, color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Average Daily Return: {avg_daily_return:.2f}')
    ax.set_xlabel('Date')
    ax.set_ylabel('Daily Return')
    ax.set_title('What is the average daily return on investment?')
    ax.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
